00:19:47,229 --> 00:19:49,565
Oh, this dream is ruining my life.

253
00:19:49,648 --> 00:19:51,608
Mine too.

254
00:19:51,692 --> 00:19:53,777
Every night, Stef.

255
00:19:53,861 --> 00:19:55,529
God, I'm not getting any sleep.

256
00:19:55,612 --> 00:19:56,864
Shit, I'm sorry.

257
00:19:58,365 --> 00:20:00,909
Um, can I tell you something?

258
00:20:02,703 --> 00:20:04,329
Yeah, what's up?

259
00:20:05,163 --> 00:20:08,542
So, the woman in my dream.
Her name is Iris, right?

260
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:09,710
Okay.

261
00:20:10,752 --> 00:20:12,254
That was my grandmother's name.

262
00:20:12,337 --> 00:20:15,883
I, uh... I think I'm dreaming about her.

263
00:20:15,966 --> 00:20:16,967
Are you serious?

264
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:19,177
Yeah. The thing is,
I never even met her.

265
00:20:19,261 --> 00:20:21,054
I don't even know if she's alive.

266
00:20:21,138 --> 00:20:22,306
Okay, well...

267
00:20:22,973 --> 00:20:26,476
either go home
and find out about Grandma

268
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:28,729
and hope that stops the dreams,

269
00:20:28,812 --> 00:20:31,940
or stay here
and die in your sleep for real.

270
00:20:33,066 --> 00:20:34,943
Because I will murder you.

271
00:20:35,027 --> 00:20:36,737
- I'm sorry.

272
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:38,906
- Yeah, yeah, okay.
- Love you.

273
00:20:39,615 --> 00:20:41,575
Yeah. Love you too.

274
00:20:41,658 --> 00:20:43,201
- Go home.
- Yeah.

275
00:20:44,036 --> 00:20:45,037
Quietly.

276
00:20:59,551 --> 00:21:00,719
Okay.

277
00:21:16,944 --> 00:21:18,028
Okay.

278
00:21:19,237 --> 00:21:21,281
- Hey, there she is!
- Hey, Dad.

279
00:21:21,365 --> 00:21:24,326
Welcome home, sweetie.
So glad you're here.

280
00:21:24,409 --> 00:21:25,911
- Yeah, me too.
- I missed you so much.

281
00:21:25,994 --> 00:21:27,079
I know.

282
00:21:27,162 --> 00:21:28,664
Oh, so great to see you.

283
00:21:28,747 --> 00:21:31,124
- Thank you, thank you.
- Let me take that for you.

284
00:21:31,208 --> 00:21:32,250
Hey, sorry.

285
00:21:32,334 --> 00:21:36,171
Charlie took your room a while ago
and my files are in his room,

286
00:21:36,254 --> 00:21:39,508
so I made up the pullout for you.
Is that okay?

287
00:21:39,591 --> 00:21:41,551
Yeah, yeah.
No, that sounds totally fine.

288
00:21:42,302 --> 00:21:46,181
Uh, hey, do we still have that box
of Mom's old stuff?

289
00:21:46,264 --> 00:21:49,893
It had, uh, some photos,
like an address book

290
00:21:49,977 --> 00:21:51,812
with phone numbers in it.

291
00:21:51,895 --> 00:21:53,230
Uh, why do you want that?

292
00:21:53,313 --> 00:21:54,481
Oh, it's not a big deal.

293
00:21:54,564 --> 00:21:56,692
I just thought I saw it
lying around here somewhere.

294
00:21:59,236 --> 00:22:00,654
Stefani, what's going on?

295
00:22:02,572 --> 00:22:05,575
Okay, this is going to sound
really, really weird,

296
00:22:05,659 --> 00:22:09,746
but I just need to find Mom's mom, Iris.

297
00:22:13,834 --> 00:22:16,420
Uh, okay. Yeah, that is weird.

298
00:22:17,671 --> 00:22:20,298
And you know,
I got rid of those boxes years ago

299
00:22:20,382 --> 00:22:21,675
after your mom left.

300
00:22:22,426 --> 00:22:23,969
- Oh, hi, Charlie.

301
00:22:24,052 --> 00:22:25,053
- Hey.

302
00:22:26,304 --> 00:22:30,392
Um, "Hi, Stef. How are you?
It's so nice to see you."

303
00:22:31,184 --> 00:22:32,394
Yeah, sure.

304
00:22:32,477 --> 00:22:34,312
Uh, I'm going to the cousins'.

305
00:22:34,396 --> 00:22:36,648
Whoa. Now?
Look, your sister just got home.

306
00:22:36,732 --> 00:22:38,066
- I thought we...
- Well, I had plans.

307
00:22:38,150 --> 00:22:39,776
Actually, you know what?
I can drive you.

308
00:22:39,860 --> 00:22:41,695
I was wanting to see them anyways.

309
00:22:41,778 --> 00:22:42,779
It's fine.

310
00:22:42,863 --> 00:22:45,365
Hey. If you're going
to see your cousins,

311
00:22:45,449 --> 00:22:47,659
please don't talk about Iris
to Uncle Howard.

312
00:22:48,368 --> 00:22:50,245
Yeah. Yeah, no problem.

313
00:22:50,328 --> 00:22:51,663
All right.

314
00:22:51,747 --> 00:22:53,623
- Bye. Love you.
- Love you too.

315
00:22:54,458 --> 00:22:56,460
- Charlie?

316
00:22:58,128 --> 00:23:00,422
Charlie... Can you just take
these out, please?

317
00:23:00,505 --> 00:23:01,757
Ow. Stef!

318
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:03,717
I'm trying to talk to you.
What's your problem?

319
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:04,968
What?

320
00:23:05,052 --> 00:23:08,472
You haven't said anything
this entire time.

321
00:23:08,555 --> 00:23:09,556
Wha...

322
00:23:10,807 --> 00:23:12,267
Stef, why are you here?

323
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:14,644
I mean, you only come home for holidays.

324
00:23:14,728 --> 00:23:16,188
Okay, I have to tell you something.

325
00:23:16,813 --> 00:23:18,899
But you have to promise not to tell Dad.

326
00:23:20,525 --> 00:23:21,735
What, are you pregnant?

327
00:23:21,818 --> 00:23:23,862
No, I'm not pregnant, Charlie.

328
00:23:23,945 --> 00:23:25,697
- I don't know.
- Why would you even...?

329
00:23:25,781 --> 00:23:27,407
That's not... I mean, you're in college.

330
00:23:27,491 --> 00:23:29,743
Okay, can you just promise me
you won't tell Dad?

331
00:23:29,826 --> 00:23:32,704
- Why would I tell Dad?
- It's serious, Charlie.

332
00:23:32,788 --> 00:23:34,372
All right.

333
00:23:40,087 --> 00:23:41,505
Okay. Um...

334
00:23:44,382 --> 00:23:47,469
I am on academic probation.

335
00:23:50,806 --> 00:23:52,015
Whoa.

336
00:23:53,892 --> 00:23:56,436
What? Charlie, stop laughing!
If I don't get my grades up...

337
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:58,396
It's kind of a big moment for me.

338
00:23:58,480 --> 00:23:59,815
This is kind of funny.

339
00:23:59,898 --> 00:24:02,400
Straight A's. You're a class president.

340
00:24:02,484 --> 00:24:03,902
Miss Valedictorian
is failing out of school.

341
00:24:03,985 --> 00:24:05,070
Charlie, it's not funny.

342
00:24:05,153 --> 00:24:07,405
If I don't get my grades up,
I will lose my scholarship.

343
00:24:07,489 --> 00:24:08,490
Oh.

344
00:24:09,866 --> 00:24:11,451
- That blows. Sorry.
- Mm-hmm.

345
00:24:12,536 --> 00:24:13,578
What happened?

346
00:24:14,454 --> 00:24:15,789
I mean, I can't sleep.

347
00:24:15,872 --> 00:24:16,832
Every time I close my eyes,

348
00:24:16,915 --> 00:24:20,919
I have this same recurring
nightmare about Iris.

349
00:24:22,212 --> 00:24:24,047
Our grandmother. I don't...

350
00:24:25,507 --> 00:24:27,259
I mean, it has to mean something.

351
00:24:27,342 --> 00:24:28,593
I don't know.

352
00:24:28,677 --> 00:24:29,970
I dream weird things.

353
00:24:31,763 --> 00:24:34,558
I dreamed a hot dog ate me last night.

354
00:24:34,641 --> 00:24:35,684
What? That is...

355
00:24:35,767 --> 00:24:37,519
Like the hot dog was eating me.

356
00:24:37,602 --> 00:24:38,603
Okay.

357
00:24:43,358 --> 00:24:45,026
Dude, can you just do something?

358
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:46,111
Dude, calm down, all right?

359
00:24:46,194 --> 00:24:47,571
- We'll find him.
- Just move a little bit.

360
00:24:47,654 --> 00:24:49,865
I can't pause, all right?
It's an online match. Are you serious?

361
00:24:49,948 --> 00:24:52,492
- I have to look under this.
- Can you do me a kindness? Fuck off.

362
00:24:52,576 --> 00:24:53,994
You remember
what happened last time?

363
00:24:54,077 --> 00:24:55,245
It's a ranked match!

364
00:24:55,328 --> 00:24:57,455
- What's going on?
- I can't find Paco.

365
00:24:57,539 --> 00:24:58,790
Dude, again?

366
00:24:58,874 --> 00:25:00,500
Wait, who's Paco?

367
00:25:00,584 --> 00:25:02,919
No way! Hey, cuz!

368
00:25:03,003 --> 00:25:05,547
Oh my gosh. Hey, can you help us look?

369
00:25:05,630 --> 00:25:07,174
And just watch your feet
where you're stepping.

370
00:25:07,257 --> 00:25:08,425
Yeah, yeah, sure.

371
00:25:08,508 --> 00:25:10,677
I just...
I got to talk to your dad first.

372
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:12,012
What the fuck you doing home?

373
00:25:12,095 --> 00:25:14,347
Oh, dude, she's flunking out of school.

374
00:25:14,431 --> 00:25:16,933
- Charlie.
- Hey, welcome to the club.

375
00:25:17,017 --> 00:25:18,602
Erik, dude, have you looked anywhere?

376
00:25:18,685 --> 00:25:19,728
Paco's not upstairs!

377
00:25:20,896 --> 00:25:22,731
- Oh. But look who's down here.
- Hi, Julia.

378
00:25:22,814 --> 00:25:24,691
- Oh my gosh. I'm so sorry...
- How you been?

379
00:25:24,774 --> 00:25:26,943
- Charlie!
- Jules!

380
00:25:27,027 --> 00:25:28,320
There's my little Romeo.

381
00:25:28,403 --> 00:25:31,031
So, wait, how did
the promposal with Jenny go?

382
00:25:31,114 --> 00:25:34,034
- Dude, she said yes.
- Oh my God. Stop. Okay, wait.

383
00:25:34,117 --> 00:25:35,702
Who's, uh... Who's Jenny?

384
00:25:36,995 --> 00:25:39,039
Oh, he met her in junior lifeguards.

385
00:25:39,122 --> 00:25:40,332
Junior lifeguards?

386
00:25:40,415 --> 00:25:42,959
Charlie, I didn't know
you were doing junior lifeguards.

387
00:25:43,043 --> 00:25:44,044
You didn't tell me that.

388
00:25:44,127 --> 00:25:45,378
Okay, so what are you going to wear?

389
00:25:45,462 --> 00:25:47,797
Um, I'm just going
to keep it simple.

390
00:25:47,881 --> 00:25:49,883
- You know, black blazer...
- Okay, yeah, yeah.

391
00:25:49,966 --> 00:25:52,093
- ...but with like a fun bowtie.
- I like it.

392
00:25:54,888 --> 00:25:58,642
Stef! Stefani! Oh my gosh!

393
00:25:58,725 --> 00:26:00,977
- Hi, honey.
- Hi, Aunt Brenda.

394
00:26:01,061 --> 00:26:02,520
- How long are you here for?
- Not long.

395
00:26:02,604 --> 00:26:04,272
Is Uncle Howard around?

396
00:26:04,356 --> 00:26:06,233
Yeah. Yeah, he's out back. I'll get him.

397
00:26:08,068 --> 00:26:10,111
Howard! Stefani's here. Come in!

398
00:26:10,195 --> 00:26:11,696
- Great!

399
00:26:13,406 --> 00:26:15,450
You look a little tired.
Is everything okay?

400
00:26:15,533 --> 00:26:17,786
- Oh.
- Stefi! Look at you!

401
00:26:17,869 --> 00:26:19,079
- Hey!
- Come here, come here.

402
00:26:19,162 --> 00:26:20,413
Oh, sweetie.

403
00:26:20,497 --> 00:26:22,415
Oh, so good to see you.
Hey, are you hungry?

404
00:26:22,499 --> 00:26:23,750
I was just gonna make some lunch.

405
00:26:23,833 --> 00:26:24,918
No, actually.

406
00:26:25,001 --> 00:26:26,628
I came here
because I wanted to talk to you

407
00:26:26,711 --> 00:26:29,005
about your mother, Iris.

408
00:26:29,089 --> 00:26:30,924
I know you don't
like to talk about her...

409
00:26:31,007 --> 00:26:32,217
There's not much to tell.

410
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,635
Hey, kids, come on, lunch!

411
00:26:33,718 --> 00:26:38,640
It's just that I've been having
this recurring nightmare about her.

412
00:26:38,723 --> 00:26:40,767
Oh, honey.
It's probably just stress.

413
00:26:40,850 --> 00:26:42,269
You should try Melatonin.

414
00:26:42,352 --> 00:26:43,937
Okay, but the weird thing is

415
00:26:44,020 --> 00:26:48,149
I've been dreaming about a real place
from 50 years ago.

416
00:26:48,233 --> 00:26:50,360
It was like a restaurant
called the Sky View.

417
00:26:53,697 --> 00:26:54,990
You know what it is.

418
00:26:55,073 --> 00:26:56,866
Did Iris tell you about it?

419
00:26:57,701 --> 00:26:59,786
What did she say? Did she say anything?

420
00:26:59,869 --> 00:27:01,246
Maybe if I could talk to her...

421
00:27:01,329 --> 00:27:02,455
Talk to who?

422
00:27:02,539 --> 00:27:04,499
Oh, Stef is dreaming about Grandma Iris.

423
00:27:04,582 --> 00:27:07,377
- Ooh, Psycho Granny?
- I thought she was dead.

424
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:09,129
Well, she's dead to us.

425
00:27:09,212 --> 00:27:10,171
Yeah, Stefi.

426
00:27:10,255 --> 00:27:13,800
Iris Campbell is a very deeply
disturbed woman. End of story.

427
00:27:13,883 --> 00:27:15,010
Look, if I could just talk to her,

428
00:27:15,093 --> 00:27:17,345
then maybe
I can get these dreams to stop.

429
00:27:17,429 --> 00:27:18,722
- Stef, just drop it.
- I don't get it.

430
00:27:18,805 --> 00:27:21,141
- What happened that was so bad?
- For one thing,

431
00:27:21,224 --> 00:27:22,851
she's the reason
that your mother is so screwed up.

432
00:27:22,934 --> 00:27:24,102
- What?
- Look, I just don't want to

433
00:27:24,185 --> 00:27:25,312
talk about this anymore. Okay?

434
00:27:25,395 --> 00:27:27,605
Uncle Howard, please.
I just need to know.

435
00:27:27,689 --> 00:27:29,983
Look, Stefi.

436
00:27:32,319 --> 00:27:33,653
After our father died...

437
00:27:34,738 --> 00:27:37,073
Iris just snapped.

438
00:27:38,199 --> 00:27:39,909
She wouldn't let us go to school.

439
00:27:39,993 --> 00:27:42,245
She locked us inside the house.

440
00:27:42,329 --> 00:27:46,082
She obsessed about all the horrific ways
we could die.

441
00:27:46,166 --> 00:27:50,211
And eventually it got so bad,
I mean, so bad,

442
00:27:50,295 --> 00:27:51,671
that the State came in

443
00:27:51,755 --> 00:27:53,798
and they took your mother and I
away from her.

444
00:27:54,591 --> 00:27:55,633
But it didn't end there.

445
00:27:55,717 --> 00:27:57,594
She tracked us all through foster care,

446
00:27:57,677 --> 00:27:59,554
and when the kids were born,

447
00:27:59,637 --> 00:28:02,557
she started sending us
these horrible letters

448
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:04,059
that were full of obituaries

449
00:28:04,142 --> 00:28:06,269
and these disturbing pictures
of dead bodies.

450
00:28:06,353 --> 00:28:09,189
We had to move
so she couldn't contact us anymore.

451
00:28:10,732 --> 00:28:11,775
So, uh...

452
00:28:14,152 --> 00:28:16,488
Do you still have
any of those letters though?

453
00:28:19,824 --> 00:28:20,825
Stefi.

454
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:23,286
Listen to me.

455
00:28:23,370 --> 00:28:26,831
That woman is a sick
and dangerous person.

456
00:28:27,791 --> 00:28:30,126
And for your well-being and your safety,

457
00:28:30,710 --> 00:28:32,212
stay the hell away from her.

458
00:28:32,879 --> 00:28:33,797
Uh...

459
00:28:38,885 --> 00:28:40,178
I found Paco!

460
00:28:40,261 --> 00:28:41,596
Oh! Thank God!

461
00:28:41,679 --> 00:28:44,599
I'm sure he'd love to be
in the living room right now.

462
00:28:44,682 --> 00:28:47,060
- He was in the pantry.
- Come on, guys. Let's go.

463
00:28:47,143 --> 00:28:48,645
How did he even get in there?

464
00:28:49,521 --> 00:28:50,688
I need you to help me.

465
00:28:52,357 --> 00:28:55,360
You heard your uncle. Just let it go.

466
00:28:55,443 --> 00:28:56,569
Just let it go.

467
00:28:57,862 --> 00:28:58,905
You don't understand.

468
00:28:58,988 --> 00:29:02,075
My whole life is falling apart
because of this dream.

469
00:29:02,158 --> 00:29:05,412
And not only that,
I feel like I'm losing my mind.

470
00:29:05,495 --> 00:29:07,664
Please, you are the only person
who can help me.

471
00:29:07,747 --> 00:29:10,750
Howard would never forgive me
if I put you in touch with Iris.

472
00:29:11,709 --> 00:29:12,669
Please.

473
00:29:19,342 --> 00:29:20,552
Whatever you do,

474
00:29:20,635 --> 00:29:25,181
do not look in the bottom drawer
of the dining room cabinet.

475
00:31:03,655 --> 00:31:04,781
Hi. Um...

476
00:31:05,615 --> 00:31:08,243
I'm here to see Iris Campbell.

477
00:31:08,326 --> 00:31:09,702
<i>Did you not see the signs?</i>

478
00:31:09,786 --> 00:31:12,497
Uh... Yeah. Yes, I did, but...

479
00:31:12,580 --> 00:31:15,667
<i>Then get the fuck out of here.
No visitors.</i>

480
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:16,876
I'm your granddaughter.

481
00:31:17,752 --> 00:31:18,878
<i>Stefani.</i>

482
00:31:22,131 --> 00:31:25,552
<i>Empty your pockets.
Phone, keys, everything.</i>

483
00:31:25,635 --> 00:31:27,470
Well, I'm not dangerous.

484
00:31:28,263 --> 00:31:29,973
It's not you I'm afraid of.

485
00:31:31,432 --> 00:31:32,809
- Uh...

486
00:32:48,426 --> 00:32:49,969
Come in slowly.

487
00:33:10,156 --> 00:33:12,367
Shut the door. Quick, quick, quick!

488
00:33:15,745 --> 00:33:16,829
Don't move.

489
00:33:23,795 --> 00:33:24,962
Oh my God.

490
00:33:26,464 --> 00:33:27,465
It really is you.

491
00:33:30,426 --> 00:33:32,261
I can see your mother in you.

492
00:33:34,681 --> 00:33:35,973
Hi. I'm Stefani...

493
00:33:36,057 --> 00:33:39,519
Stop! Stop. Don't move.

494
00:33:39,602 --> 00:33:41,062
Not until I tell you.

495
00:33:43,314 --> 00:33:44,524
Trying to trick me, aren't you?

496
00:33:46,734 --> 00:33:48,820
Getting me
to let my guard down.

497
00:33:48,903 --> 00:33:49,904
I...

498
00:33:50,655 --> 00:33:52,031
There you go. Come on.

499
00:33:53,282 --> 00:33:54,701
Come here. Sit.

500
00:33:56,494 --> 00:33:57,537
Okay. Um...

501
00:33:57,620 --> 00:33:58,663
Sit.

502
00:33:59,914 --> 00:34:00,915
That's it.

503
00:34:02,250 --> 00:34:05,128
So, how is Darlene?

504
00:34:05,712 --> 00:34:07,797
- Your mom okay?
- Oh. Uh...

505
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:09,590
No. Uh, I don't know.

506
00:34:09,674 --> 00:34:14,887
She, uh... she left when I was ten,
so we don't see her anymore.

507
00:34:14,971 --> 00:34:15,930
Oh.

508
00:34:19,684 --> 00:34:21,894
But you saw my letters.
That's why you're here, right?

509
00:34:22,729 --> 00:34:24,147
No. Um...

510
00:34:25,356 --> 00:34:28,818
I'm actually here because
I've been dreaming about the Sky View.

511
00:34:28,901 --> 00:34:31,362
- What?
- Yeah.

512
00:34:31,446 --> 00:34:33,281
Yeah, every single night
for the past two months.

513
00:34:33,364 --> 00:34:35,241
It's the same dream.

514
00:34:35,324 --> 00:34:38,786
In it, you're on a date,
but then the dance floor breaks

515
00:34:38,870 --> 00:34:41,372
and then there's an explosion
and then you...

516
00:34:41,456 --> 00:34:43,291
Fall. And die.

517
00:34:43,374 --> 00:34:45,626
Yeah. Yeah, everyone dies.

518
00:34:46,544 --> 00:34:47,962
It wasn't just your dream.

519
00:34:49,088 --> 00:34:50,840
It was my premonition.

520
00:34:51,758 --> 00:34:53,843
Years ago, at the Sky View,

521
00:34:53,926 --> 00:34:56,596
I got a glimpse into the future

522
00:34:56,679 --> 00:34:58,848
and saw what Death was about to do.

523
00:35:03,811 --> 00:35:06,689
I was going to do this at dinner,
but seeing as we have this view...

524
00:35:10,693 --> 00:35:13,488
Hey! Don't throw that penny.
It could kill somebody.

525
00:35:13,571 --> 00:35:14,989
Oh, I'm so sorry. Of course.

526
00:35:15,531 --> 00:35:16,532
Fat ass.

527
00:35:16,616 --> 00:35:19,160
These past few years
have been absolutely magical.

528
00:35:19,243 --> 00:35:21,871
And that's all because of you.

529
00:35:21,954 --> 00:35:23,206
No, no, no. I...

530
00:35:24,749 --> 00:35:26,000
This isn't right. I...

531
00:35:26,083 --> 00:35:27,335
Is that a no?

532
00:35:28,836 --> 00:35:30,463
Everyone's going to die.

533
00:35:30,546 --> 00:35:32,548
No, the whole building
is going to come down.

534
00:35:32,632 --> 00:35:34,258
Are you serious?

535
00:35:36,177 --> 00:35:37,887
- The penny.
- Iris?

536
00:35:37,970 --> 00:35:39,597
- Give me that!
- What the hell, lady?

537
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:41,140
- Give it to me!
- What are you doing?

538
00:35:42,141 --> 00:35:43,810
What the fuck is wrong with you?

539
00:35:43,893 --> 00:35:47,897
♪ <i>Well... ♪</i>

540
00:35:47,980 --> 00:35:48,981
Iris?

541
00:35:49,065 --> 00:35:51,275
<i>- ♪ You know you make me wanna ♪
- ♪ Shout ♪</i>

542
00:35:51,359 --> 00:35:52,527
<i>- ♪ Kick my heels up and ♪
- ♪ Shout ♪</i>

543
00:35:52,610 --> 00:35:53,528
Move!

544
00:35:54,862 --> 00:35:56,447
<i>- ♪ Throw my head back and ♪
- ♪ Shout ♪</i>

545
00:35:56,531 --> 00:35:57,990
<i>- ♪ Come on now ♪
- ♪ Shout ♪</i>

546
00:35:58,074 --> 00:35:59,617
<i>♪ Don't forget to say you will ♪</i>

547
00:36:00,868 --> 00:36:03,538
<i>♪ Don't forget to say yeah, yeah
Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪</i>

548
00:36:03,621 --> 00:36:05,832
Stop playing! Stop playing!

549
00:36:05,915 --> 00:36:07,917
<i>Everyone needs
to get off the dance floor!</i>

550
00:36:08,835 --> 00:36:11,212
<i>The glass is about to break.
Everyone needs to get off now!</i>

551
00:36:11,295 --> 00:36:12,547
- Ma'am.
- Wait! No!

552
00:36:12,630 --> 00:36:14,131
Get off the dance floor!

553
00:36:14,215 --> 00:36:16,050
- Iris!
- You need to get off!

554
00:36:16,133 --> 00:36:17,343
Get off!

555
00:36:21,931 --> 00:36:24,016
I saved a lot of lives
that night.

556
00:36:25,017 --> 00:36:26,811
Lives that were never meant to be saved.

557
00:36:28,563 --> 00:36:30,231
They closed the restaurant after that.

558
00:36:31,232 --> 00:36:34,360
Said it needed additional renovations.

559
00:36:35,403 --> 00:36:37,280
But it never reopened.

560
00:36:37,363 --> 00:36:39,156
Eventually they tore it down.

561
00:36:39,240 --> 00:36:41,534
Wait, so you stopped the disaster.

562
00:36:42,660 --> 00:36:44,120
Yes.

563
00:36:47,582 --> 00:36:49,876
But Death doesn't like it
when you fuck with his plans.

564
00:36:50,459 --> 00:36:52,086
So, over the years, he came back

565
00:36:52,169 --> 00:36:55,047
and he killed everyone
who was there that night.

566
00:36:55,131 --> 00:36:56,465
Including my Paul.

567
00:36:59,260 --> 00:37:02,847
Wait a minute. I'm sorry. Did you...
Did you say Death came back?

568
00:37:02,930 --> 00:37:05,433
He's a relentless son of a bitch.

569
00:37:05,516 --> 00:37:07,435
Won't stop until he finishes the job,

570
00:37:07,518 --> 00:37:09,854
but I taught myself
how to see him coming.

571
00:37:10,438 --> 00:37:13,149
To anticipate his every move.

572
00:37:13,232 --> 00:37:16,027
I've been keeping him at bay
for years now.

573
00:37:17,361 --> 00:37:19,155
But now he's got me. Cancer.

574
00:37:19,238 --> 00:37:20,489
Oh. Uh...

575
00:37:20,573 --> 00:37:22,533
- Believe that shit?
- Sorry.

576
00:37:22,617 --> 00:37:24,368
Got the diagnosis two months ago.

577
00:37:25,661 --> 00:37:27,622
Wait, that's when
I started having my dream.

578
00:37:27,705 --> 00:37:29,040
See? It's a sign.

579
00:37:29,123 --> 00:37:32,043
Okay, but why am I dreaming
about what you saw?

580
00:37:32,126 --> 00:37:34,629
Maybe my cancer
passed my premonition onto you.

581
00:37:34,712 --> 00:37:36,672
Maybe it's fate's demented
sense of humor.

582
00:37:36,756 --> 00:37:38,007
Who the hell knows.

583
00:37:38,090 --> 00:37:41,218
What matters
is that when the Universe speaks,

584
00:37:41,302 --> 00:37:42,845
you pay attention.

585
00:37:55,149 --> 00:37:56,442
I see you, you fuck.

586
00:38:01,989 --> 00:38:05,326
- Um... Who are you talking to?
- Death.

587
00:38:06,285 --> 00:38:08,537
He thinks I'm distracted
because you're here.

588
00:38:09,872 --> 00:38:12,249
I have to teach you
everything in this book.

589
00:38:12,333 --> 00:38:14,043
It'll take some time
to learn the basics,

590
00:38:14,126 --> 00:38:15,628
so you'll need to stay here.

591
00:38:15,711 --> 00:38:16,712
Stay here?

592
00:38:16,796 --> 00:38:17,880
The outside world is too dangerous.

593
00:38:17,964 --> 00:38:19,966
I haven't stepped out there in 20 years.

594
00:38:20,049 --> 00:38:22,051
In here, we can be safe.

595
00:38:23,552 --> 00:38:24,762
Oh.

596
00:38:24,845 --> 00:38:26,138
See that?

597
00:38:26,222 --> 00:38:27,640
Yeah.

598
00:38:27,723 --> 00:38:31,060
This is all my research.
My life's work.

599
00:38:31,143 --> 00:38:34,188
Look, I'm sorry. I can't stay here.

600
00:38:34,271 --> 00:38:36,273
I have to get back to school,

601
00:38:36,357 --> 00:38:38,442
but, you know,
I'll come back and I'll visit.

602
00:38:38,526 --> 00:38:41,362
No, I'm sick!
I won't be alive that long.

603
00:38:41,445 --> 00:38:42,822
You can't leave.

604
00:38:42,905 --> 00:38:43,990
Don't you see?

605
00:38:44,782 --> 00:38:46,909
Death is coming for our family.

606
00:38:47,827 --> 00:38:49,578
Uh...

607
00:38:50,246 --> 00:38:51,622
You don't believe me.

608
00:38:51,706 --> 00:38:56,085
No. Um... I think I made a mistake.

609
00:38:56,168 --> 00:38:58,838
I think it was probably just a dream.

610
00:38:58,921 --> 00:39:01,173
No, wait. At least take the book.

611
00:39:01,924 --> 00:39:02,925
Stefani!

612
00:39:03,634 --> 00:39:04,802
Stefani!

613
00:39:27,950 --> 00:39:29,994
Stefani! Stop!

614
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:33,205
Look, I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have come here.

615
00:39:33,956 --> 00:39:36,167
This book is a lifeline.

616
00:39:36,250 --> 00:39:37,126
It will show you

617
00:39:37,209 --> 00:39:38,961
everything you need to know
to keep our family safe.

618
00:39:40,963 --> 00:39:42,590
You still don't believe me.

619
00:39:47,178 --> 00:39:48,137
Step back.

620
00:39:48,220 --> 00:39:49,597
What? Why?

621
00:39:51,974 --> 00:39:53,392
Seeing is believing.

622
00:40:15,456 --> 00:40:18,584
Hey, Stef. Her face
really explode right in front of you?

623
00:40:18,667 --> 00:40:21,003
- Erik! Just leave her alone.
- I'm...

624
00:40:21,921 --> 00:40:23,631
It's my bad, Stef. I'm just curious.

625
00:40:25,508 --> 00:40:28,803
Hey. How are you holding up?

626
00:40:30,721 --> 00:40:32,223
I'm sorry, Uncle Howard.

627
00:40:33,766 --> 00:40:36,727
You were right about Iris.
I... I never should've went there.

628
00:40:36,811 --> 00:40:39,021
Honey, there's no need to apologize.

629
00:40:39,105 --> 00:40:41,982
I'm so sorry you had to go through that.

630
00:40:46,195 --> 00:40:48,030
She said something to me
before she died.

631
00:40:48,114 --> 00:40:49,865
She said Death was coming
for our family.

632
00:40:49,949 --> 00:40:52,743
That's crazy, right?

633
00:40:52,827 --> 00:40:53,994
Oh my God.

634
00:40:55,121 --> 00:40:56,288
I can't believe it.

635
00:40:56,372 --> 00:40:59,291
I emailed her.
I just didn't think she'd show up. I...

636
00:41:00,084 --> 00:41:01,085
Come on.

637
00:41:09,468 --> 00:41:10,469
Is that, um...

638
00:41:12,263 --> 00:41:13,264
Is that Mom?

639
00:41:14,765 --> 00:41:15,766
Yeah.

640
00:41:21,355 --> 00:41:22,439
Darlene!

641
00:41:24,525 --> 00:41:26,610
- Wow.
- Um...

642
00:41:28,404 --> 00:41:29,572
I can come back.

643
00:41:29,655 --> 00:41:31,407
Oh, don't be ridiculous.
Come on.

644
00:41:31,490 --> 00:41:32,825
Get down here. Come here.

645
00:41:36,328 --> 00:41:37,955
Think she'll come
to the barbecue?

646
00:41:41,542 --> 00:41:43,169
Stef. Hey, wait up.

647
00:41:43,252 --> 00:41:45,212
If she's going
to Uncle Howard's house, then I'm not.

648
00:41:45,296 --> 00:41:46,338
You can get a ride with Dad.

649
00:41:46,422 --> 00:41:48,757
Uh...
You're not even going to talk to her?

650
00:41:48,841 --> 00:41:49,842
Come on.

651
00:41:49,925 --> 00:41:51,343
You don't remember her like I do.

652
00:41:51,927 --> 00:41:53,304
- Just give her a chance.
- Why?

653
00:41:54,180 --> 00:41:56,056
Charlie, she abandoned us

654
00:41:56,140 --> 00:41:58,225
and now she rolls in here
after all these years,

655
00:41:58,309 --> 00:42:00,352
and wants to act like nothing happened?

656
00:42:02,021 --> 00:42:05,232
Yeah. Because who would do that? Right?

657
00:42:05,816 --> 00:42:06,817
Wait. What?

658
00:42:06,901 --> 00:42:09,069
- Nothing. Forget it.
- No.

659
00:42:09,153 --> 00:42:10,738
No. What's that supposed to mean?

660
00:42:10,821 --> 00:42:13,741
I tried calling you
so many times and nothing.

661
00:42:13,824 --> 00:42:14,783
Same with Julia.

662
00:42:14,867 --> 00:42:16,702
You used to be best friends.
You don't even talk anymore.

663
00:42:16,785 --> 00:42:18,621
Okay, I'm sorry.

664
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:21,624
I've just been distracted
the last couple of months

665
00:42:21,707 --> 00:42:22,791
because of this nightmare.

666
00:42:22,875 --> 00:42:25,419
Okay, but what about before that?
It's been like this ever since you left.

667
00:42:27,087 --> 00:42:29,506
You're mad at Mom,
but you haven't been around either.

668
00:42:29,590 --> 00:42:30,716
I'm not like her!

669
00:42:31,800 --> 00:42:32,801
Okay?

670
00:42:33,969 --> 00:42:35,221
I'm not crazy.

671
00:42:38,474 --> 00:42:40,851
Yeah, you're right. You're not crazy.

672
00:42:42,603 --> 00:42:43,687
You just don't care.

673
00:44:10,607 --> 00:44:12,776
Now you got it. Watch out for splinters.

674
00:44:27,875 --> 00:44:29,376
Hey, there she is!

675
00:44:30,294 --> 00:44:31,378
Hey!

676
00:44:31,462 --> 00:44:34,048
Come here. So glad you made it.

677
00:44:35,716 --> 00:44:37,509
You know, I didn't think
you were actually going to come.

678
00:44:37,593 --> 00:44:38,969
Thank you for inviting me.

679
00:44:39,053 --> 00:44:40,346
Of course. Come on in.

680
00:44:40,429 --> 00:44:42,306
Hey, everybody! Come on! Come on over!

681
00:44:44,058 --> 00:44:45,726
- I made cookies.
- That's great!

682
00:44:46,393 --> 00:44:48,937
- Can I try one?
- Yes, of course.

683
00:44:54,985 --> 00:44:57,112
- Does this have peanut butter?
- Yeah.

684
00:45:00,240 --> 00:45:02,076
Are you trying
to kill my brother?

685
00:45:02,951 --> 00:45:05,120
- Oh my God. Bobby's allergic.
- Yeah.

686
00:45:05,204 --> 00:45:06,622
I totally forgot.
I'm so sorry.

687
00:45:06,705 --> 00:45:08,916
You know, the most important thing
is that you're here, so...

688
00:45:08,999 --> 00:45:11,168
Uh, Bobby Bartender, drinks!
Drinks all around!

689
00:45:19,968 --> 00:45:21,011
Family.

690
00:45:22,137 --> 00:45:24,556
You don't get to pick the one you get,

691
00:45:24,640 --> 00:45:27,393
just got to love the one that you got.

692
00:45:29,144 --> 00:45:31,063
Now, our mother...

693
00:45:31,897 --> 00:45:34,149
she lived alone
until the day that she died.

694
00:45:34,733 --> 00:45:38,195
And her death should
be a reminder to all of us

695
00:45:38,278 --> 00:45:39,613
to enjoy life

696
00:45:39,696 --> 00:45:41,907
and spend the time
that we have together.

697
00:45:44,493 --> 00:45:46,328
Because we're not going to get any back.

698
00:45:47,746 --> 00:45:50,541
- I love you guys.
- Aw.

699
00:45:50,624 --> 00:45:53,419
Cheers to that! Cheers!

700
00:45:58,924 --> 00:46:00,384
- This is strong.

701
00:46:01,385 --> 00:46:02,678
What did you put in there?

702
00:46:03,679 --> 00:46:06,014
- Julia? Oh, Jules!

703
00:46:06,098 --> 00:46:07,307
Are you all right?

704
00:46:07,391 --> 00:46:09,935
Oh my God.
There was a bug in there. Ugh.

705
00:46:10,519 --> 00:46:11,687
Extra protein.

706
00:46:32,708 --> 00:46:34,376
- You on?

707
00:46:36,462 --> 00:46:37,796
Oh.

708
00:46:37,880 --> 00:46:39,673
- I got it.
- I don't think you've got it.

709
00:46:39,756 --> 00:46:40,674
Oh, it's coming.

710
00:46:45,053 --> 00:46:47,181
Actually, I'm starting
a new lifeguarding job.

711
00:46:47,264 --> 00:46:48,348
- That's great.
- Yeah.

712
00:46:48,432 --> 00:46:49,766
Charlie!

713
00:46:49,850 --> 00:46:50,934
Get up here!

714
00:47:07,951 --> 00:47:09,703
- Jeez! Whoa!

715
00:47:12,247 --> 00:47:14,708
- Erik!
- Ma, grill's ready.

716
00:47:20,923 --> 00:47:23,133
Mm.

717
00:47:32,267 --> 00:47:33,352
Mind if I join you?

718
00:47:33,435 --> 00:47:35,562
Have a seat. Take a load off.

719
00:47:37,856 --> 00:47:40,025
Oh, yeah. There we go.

720
00:47:41,193 --> 00:47:42,903
It's quite the setup
you've got here.

721
00:47:43,862 --> 00:47:47,115
Well, I wanted the kids
to have a happy childhood.

722
00:47:47,199 --> 00:47:49,368
- Unlike some people I know.

723
00:47:49,451 --> 00:47:50,994
You're not talking about us, are you?

724
00:47:51,078 --> 00:47:52,538
- Oh, no.
- We had a great childhood.

725
00:47:52,621 --> 00:47:54,122
- Mm-hmm.
- I mean, look at me.

726
00:47:54,206 --> 00:47:56,375
I turned out... fabulous.

727
00:48:00,712 --> 00:48:01,713
Yep.

728
00:48:04,383 --> 00:48:05,342
Huh.

729
00:48:06,260 --> 00:48:07,261
Howard.

730
00:48:07,970 --> 00:48:09,221
- What?
- Come on. What is that?

731
00:48:09,304 --> 00:48:11,390
It looks like a house key to me.

732
00:48:12,391 --> 00:48:13,850
Come on.
You know we've got the spare room.

733
00:48:13,934 --> 00:48:14,893
I know.

734
00:48:14,977 --> 00:48:17,145
And it's got to be better
than bouncing around trailer parks.

735
00:48:25,112 --> 00:48:26,738
I don't think this is a good idea.

736
00:48:26,822 --> 00:48:28,907
It's never too late for a second chance.

737
00:48:32,494 --> 00:48:33,495
I'm sorry.

738
00:48:37,583 --> 00:48:39,626
They're better off without me.

739
00:48:42,838 --> 00:48:44,590
- Pick up, pick up. Come on.

740
00:48:46,341 --> 00:48:48,427
Okay, wait,
you bounce me or I bounce you?

741
00:48:48,510 --> 00:48:50,220
You're bouncing me,
you're bouncing me.

742
00:49:01,815 --> 00:49:04,026
Hey, Dad!
Come show us your backflip!

743
00:49:04,109 --> 00:49:06,612
- What? No, no, no.
- Yeah, come on, Uncle Howard!

744
00:49:06,695 --> 00:49:09,906
- Come on, Howard!
- Howard! Howard! Howard!

745
00:49:11,783 --> 00:49:13,035
Help him up, help him up.

746
00:49:13,118 --> 00:49:15,287
- Thank you.

747
00:49:17,456 --> 00:49:18,832
- Oh, yeah!
- There you go.

748
00:49:21,501 --> 00:49:22,461
Stop stalling.

749
00:49:22,544 --> 00:49:23,795
What's the worst thing
that could happen?

750
00:49:24,713 --> 00:49:26,256
All right. Here we go. Watch out.

751
00:49:26,340 --> 00:49:27,382
Wait! Stop!

752
00:49:36,600 --> 00:49:40,562
- Oh, nice catch, Aunt D. All right.
- All right, here we go.

753
00:49:40,646 --> 00:49:41,980
- Okay, Dad.
- Let's do it.

754
00:49:42,064 --> 00:49:44,191
- Stay away from that edge.
- Come on, Uncle Howard.

755
00:49:44,274 --> 00:49:45,651
There you go. Just like college.

756
00:49:45,734 --> 00:49:47,110
Yep, nice.

757
00:49:47,694 --> 00:49:49,738
- Mom, you watch this?
- Careful, Howard.

758
00:50:15,972 --> 00:50:18,141
Not taking it out of there.
That's cheating!

759
00:50:18,225 --> 00:50:20,644
Hey, Stefi!

760
00:50:20,727 --> 00:50:22,270
- You made it!
- Stefani.

761
00:50:23,271 --> 00:50:24,648
I'm glad you decided to come.

762
00:50:24,731 --> 00:50:26,566
Now watch the master.

763
00:50:27,776 --> 00:50:29,528
Now the whole family's here!

764
00:50:33,699 --> 00:50:35,951
I'm okay. I'm all right.

765
00:50:36,034 --> 00:50:37,119
Whoa, good.

766
00:50:41,164 --> 00:50:43,250
I'm okay. It's okay.

767
00:50:43,333 --> 00:50:45,293
- It's all right. Whoa.

768
00:50:58,807 --> 00:51:00,475
The former things
have passed away.

769
00:51:00,559 --> 00:51:03,603
Neither shall there
be mourning nor pain.

770
00:51:03,687 --> 00:51:06,898
And he shall wipe away
every tear from their eyes.

771
00:51:08,316 --> 00:51:09,568
And death shall be no more.

772
00:51:57,741 --> 00:51:58,950
Hey.

773
00:52:05,499 --> 00:52:06,917
What is all this stuff?

774
00:52:12,255 --> 00:52:13,173
Okay.

775
00:52:14,007 --> 00:52:16,551
I found these papers in Iris's book.

776
00:52:16,635 --> 00:52:21,807
They are obituaries and articles
for the people who were at the Sky View

777
00:52:21,890 --> 00:52:24,059
on the night
that Iris had her premonition.

778
00:52:25,227 --> 00:52:29,105
Each one of these people went on to die
in some weird and messed up way.

779
00:52:29,189 --> 00:52:30,482
And not only that,

780
00:52:30,565 --> 00:52:33,693
they all died in the same order
as Iris's premonition.

781
00:52:33,777 --> 00:52:36,363
Hundreds of people
were supposed to die that night,

782
00:52:36,446 --> 00:52:38,824
but Iris... Iris stopped the disaster.

783
00:52:40,075 --> 00:52:42,953
So, Death came back for them one by one.

784
00:52:44,037 --> 00:52:45,956
Since there were so many survivors,

785
00:52:46,039 --> 00:52:48,542
it took years for Death
to get to all of them.

786
00:52:48,625 --> 00:52:50,460
But eventually it got to Iris.

787
00:52:52,337 --> 00:52:54,005
I mean, she was the last to die
in the premonition.

788
00:52:55,006 --> 00:52:56,758
It was her and a little boy.

789
00:52:58,218 --> 00:52:59,719
But she was prepared.

790
00:53:00,887 --> 00:53:04,558
She single-handedly held off Death
for decades.

791
00:53:04,641 --> 00:53:05,934
Stefani, sweetie,

792
00:53:07,269 --> 00:53:09,563
I don't think this is
the appropriate time for this.

793
00:53:09,646 --> 00:53:11,022
Yeah, I mean,
none of this even has anything

794
00:53:11,106 --> 00:53:12,232
to do with us, right?

795
00:53:12,315 --> 00:53:13,567
- No.
- Why are we even here?

796
00:53:13,650 --> 00:53:15,151
No, it has everything to do with us.

797
00:53:15,235 --> 00:53:19,364
I mean, because Death took so long
to make its way through the survivors,

798
00:53:19,447 --> 00:53:20,824
these people went on to have families.

799
00:53:20,907 --> 00:53:23,159
Families that they never should've had.

800
00:53:23,743 --> 00:53:25,245
So Death took them too.

801
00:53:26,204 --> 00:53:28,832
I mean, don't you see this?

802
00:53:30,125 --> 00:53:33,420
Death is coming for us
because we were never supposed to exist.

803
00:53:34,087 --> 00:53:35,547
Okay, so, what,

804
00:53:35,630 --> 00:53:38,341
everybody in this room
is on Death's "hit list"?

805
00:53:38,425 --> 00:53:40,010
- Bobby, stop.
- That's what she's saying.

806
00:53:40,093 --> 00:53:42,012
No, Dad and Aunt Brenda are safe

807
00:53:42,095 --> 00:53:43,555
because they're not
part of Iris's bloodline.

808
00:53:44,472 --> 00:53:46,683
Okay. Following the pattern...

809
00:53:47,851 --> 00:53:51,104
Death makes its way
down each branch by age.

810
00:53:51,187 --> 00:53:53,982
So because Uncle Howard was the oldest,
it'll start with his family first.

811
00:53:54,065 --> 00:53:56,818
- Meaning, Erik, you're next.
- Go fuck yourself.

812
00:53:56,902 --> 00:53:59,112
Then it'll go for Julia, then Bobby.

813
00:54:00,822 --> 00:54:02,324
Then it'll come for our branch,

814
00:54:02,407 --> 00:54:05,827
starting with Darlene,
then me, then Charlie.

815
00:54:07,162 --> 00:54:08,246
Charlie.

816
00:54:09,539 --> 00:54:10,582
You buying this?

817
00:54:11,875 --> 00:54:12,918
I don't know.

818
00:54:13,001 --> 00:54:14,377
This is so messed up.

819
00:54:14,461 --> 00:54:15,795
I mean, you're turning our dad's death

820
00:54:15,879 --> 00:54:18,381
into some kind of fucked up
conspiracy theory.

821
00:54:18,465 --> 00:54:19,966
- What is wrong with you?
- No, no, no.

822
00:54:20,050 --> 00:54:21,635
No, it's not a conspiracy theory.

823
00:54:21,718 --> 00:54:22,844
Stef, enough.

824
00:54:22,928 --> 00:54:24,429
- We're all going to die!
- Stop!

825
00:54:24,512 --> 00:54:27,098
I can't listen to this
for one more minute.

826
00:54:27,182 --> 00:54:29,017
That crazy woman's nonsense

827
00:54:29,100 --> 00:54:32,228
has caused enough pain and suffering
for this family.

828
00:54:32,312 --> 00:54:34,064
Hang on.
Aunt Brenda, please just listen.

829
00:54:34,147 --> 00:54:35,148
For God's sake, leave it alone.

830
00:54:35,231 --> 00:54:37,359
Okay, in Iris's book
she mentions somebody

831
00:54:37,442 --> 00:54:39,319
who cheated Death and survived.

832
00:54:39,402 --> 00:54:40,528
Stefani.

833
00:54:40,612 --> 00:54:42,280
- Come on.
- Erik. No, wait.

834
00:54:42,364 --> 00:54:44,366
- I'm worried about you.
- Stop it.

835
00:54:46,034 --> 00:54:47,702
- Let me take care of this.
- Come on, Bobby.

836
00:54:47,786 --> 00:54:48,828
- Brenda.
- Let's go.

837
00:54:48,912 --> 00:54:50,413
- Brenda, I'm sorry.
- No, no, no.

838
00:54:50,497 --> 00:54:51,915
- I didn't know.
- Please.

839
00:54:51,998 --> 00:54:53,458
You believe me, right?

840
00:54:53,541 --> 00:54:54,876
- I'm sorry.
- Julia.

841
00:54:54,960 --> 00:54:56,169
Look, I love you.

842
00:54:58,213 --> 00:54:59,798
But sometimes I really hate you.

843
00:55:20,276 --> 00:55:24,030
I know how convincing
all of this can be.

844
00:55:24,739 --> 00:55:26,241
But it's not real.

845
00:55:27,242 --> 00:55:28,576
How can you say that?

846
00:55:28,660 --> 00:55:31,287
I know Iris taught you all of this.

847
00:55:31,371 --> 00:55:34,165
Don't let my mom's beliefs
derail your life...

848
00:55:35,125 --> 00:55:36,751
the same way they did mine.

849
00:55:40,296 --> 00:55:43,008
Thank you so much for that advice,

850
00:55:43,091 --> 00:55:45,260
but I really don't need a mom anymore.

851
00:55:50,181 --> 00:55:51,683
All right, open wide.

852
00:55:51,766 --> 00:55:52,934
All right, good.

853
00:55:54,978 --> 00:55:56,604
This is going to pinch, all right?
You ready?

854
00:55:56,688 --> 00:55:59,232
- Mm-hmm.
- Five, four, three...

855
00:56:02,360 --> 00:56:04,112
- ...two, one.

856
00:56:04,195 --> 00:56:05,280
Good job.

857
00:56:07,782 --> 00:56:10,493
Ready to hit the club.
Need you to lock up.

858
00:56:10,577 --> 00:56:12,203
And don't touch any of my liquor.

859
00:56:12,287 --> 00:56:14,247
No, no, you didn't say anything
about locking up.

860
00:56:14,330 --> 00:56:15,206
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

861
00:56:15,290 --> 00:56:16,541
You didn't say shit about closing, dude!

862
00:56:16,624 --> 00:56:18,001
Yeah, cry me a river.

863
00:56:18,084 --> 00:56:19,669
I hope you burn in hell!

864
00:56:22,338 --> 00:56:24,007
Do you believe that shit?

865
00:56:24,090 --> 00:56:25,341
My old man just died.

866
00:56:25,425 --> 00:56:28,928
I come in as a favor to that asshole
and now he wants me to lock up.

867
00:56:30,013 --> 00:56:31,347
- You know what that is?
- Mm-hmm.

868
00:56:31,431 --> 00:56:33,850
You know what that is?
It's inconsiderate.

869
00:56:33,933 --> 00:56:35,560
Anyway, you're all done.

870
00:56:35,643 --> 00:56:37,395
Mm-hmm. Thank you.

871
00:56:37,479 --> 00:56:38,855
Of course. Hey, five-star review, yeah?

872
00:56:38,938 --> 00:56:42,525
Like and subscribe and all the things.

873
00:58:09,154 --> 00:58:12,740
♪ <i>No
I can't forget this evening ♪</i>

874
00:58:12,824 --> 00:58:16,619
<i>♪ Or your face as you were leaving ♪</i>

875
00:58:16,703 --> 00:58:19,873
<i>♪ But I guess that's just the way ♪</i>

876
00:58:19,956 --> 00:58:22,167
<i>♪ The story goes ♪</i>

877
00:59:29,776 --> 00:59:31,945
Oh, goddamn it.

878
00:59:54,384 --> 00:59:55,885
What the fuck?

879
00:59:57,720 --> 00:59:59,264
Come on.

880
01:00:03,309 --> 01:00:04,310
Come on.

881
01:00:10,608 --> 01:00:12,402
Okay, okay.

882
01:00:12,485 --> 01:00:13,611
Okay, come on.

883
01:00:25,290 --> 01:00:26,249
Shit!

884
01:00:42,765 --> 01:00:43,683
Shit!

885
01:01:05,204 --> 01:01:07,373
Charlie, wake up. Charlie, wake...

886
01:01:07,457 --> 01:01:09,584
Charlie, wake up!

887
01:01:09,667 --> 01:01:11,085
I've been trying to call Erik all night.

888
01:01:11,169 --> 01:01:12,211
He's not answering me.

889
01:01:12,295 --> 01:01:14,255
I don't know where he is. I'm worried.

890
01:01:14,839 --> 01:01:16,215
I'm sure he's fine.

891
01:01:16,299 --> 01:01:17,508
Well, have you heard from him?

892
01:01:24,557 --> 01:01:26,768
I'm going over there.
I need to check on him.

893
01:01:28,603 --> 01:01:30,521
And you're coming too, Charlie!

894
01:01:32,940 --> 01:01:35,193
- It keeps going to voicemail.

895
01:01:36,778 --> 01:01:37,820
Is that him?

896
01:01:38,696 --> 01:01:41,449
My friend just said the tattoo parlor
burned down last night.

897
01:01:41,532 --> 01:01:42,784
What?

898
01:01:42,867 --> 01:01:44,702
- Stef, Stef, Stef!

899
01:01:45,703 --> 01:01:48,623
Ow! You trying to kill me?

900
01:01:49,207 --> 01:01:50,124
Erik?

901
01:01:50,917 --> 01:01:53,086
Oh, yeah, no, of course it's you.

902
01:01:57,131 --> 01:01:58,216
Dude!

903
01:01:58,299 --> 01:02:00,301
We heard about the fire.
We thought you were dead.

904
01:02:00,385 --> 01:02:01,928
I'm fine.

905
01:02:02,011 --> 01:02:03,679
Oh my God. Are you okay?
I was so worried about you.

906
01:02:03,763 --> 01:02:05,807
Yeah. The firefighters said
I was lucky as fuck

907
01:02:05,890 --> 01:02:07,308
that I was wearing that leather jacket.

908
01:02:07,392 --> 01:02:08,601
Barely got burned.

909
01:02:09,310 --> 01:02:10,728
Ruined my favorite jacket though.

910
01:02:10,812 --> 01:02:12,647
- What is this?
- Oh, yeah, check it out.

911
01:02:13,731 --> 01:02:15,316
I got branded.

912
01:02:15,400 --> 01:02:16,818
Sick, right?

913
01:02:16,901 --> 01:02:17,944
You like it?

914
01:02:18,027 --> 01:02:19,320
You said you were asleep.

915
01:02:19,404 --> 01:02:21,364
You were blowing up my phone
like a goddamn stalker.

916
01:02:21,447 --> 01:02:24,158
- What did you want me to do?
- No, I don't get it. You should be dead.

917
01:02:24,242 --> 01:02:26,327
Right. Yeah, yeah.

918
01:02:26,411 --> 01:02:28,746
Or, you know, maybe...

919
01:02:28,830 --> 01:02:31,833
maybe Death's not actually
coming for our family.

920
01:02:31,916 --> 01:02:34,127
Because that
would be fucking crazy.

921
01:02:34,210 --> 01:02:35,711
- Jesus!

922
01:02:35,795 --> 01:02:37,380
- Shit!

923
01:02:41,217 --> 01:02:42,552
Or maybe I'm invincible.

924
01:02:43,678 --> 01:02:44,971
- Erik.

925
01:02:45,555 --> 01:02:46,681
Erik!

926
01:02:46,764 --> 01:02:48,141
- Yeah?
- Erik, wait.

927
01:02:48,224 --> 01:02:49,684
- Stop, just wait, okay?
- Mm-hmm.

928
01:02:49,767 --> 01:02:51,227
Just because Death
didn't kill you last night,

929
01:02:51,310 --> 01:02:52,770
doesn't mean that you're safe.

930
01:02:54,814 --> 01:02:56,691
Stay away from that tree trimmer!

931
01:02:58,985 --> 01:03:02,029
Is it going to move on its own, Stef?
Is that what it's going to do?

932
01:03:02,113 --> 01:03:04,157
It could fall.

933
01:03:04,240 --> 01:03:06,617
And stay away from these kids.

934
01:03:06,701 --> 01:03:08,369
I'll take my chances.

935
01:03:08,453 --> 01:03:11,831
Stef, how's a couple kids
with a soccer ball going to kill him?

936
01:03:12,623 --> 01:03:14,459
I mean, I don't know.

937
01:03:15,042 --> 01:03:18,379
The trimmer could fall
and hit the leaf blower guy

938
01:03:18,463 --> 01:03:20,173
which causes him to...

939
01:03:20,256 --> 01:03:23,259
blow stuff into the kids' eyes
and then kick the ball into his face.

940
01:03:23,342 --> 01:03:24,927
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

941
01:03:26,262 --> 01:03:27,763
Soccer ball to my face?

942
01:03:29,182 --> 01:03:30,683
That does sound deadly.

943
01:03:31,642 --> 01:03:32,852
I should be more careful.

944
01:03:34,896 --> 01:03:36,147
- Hey!
- What's up?

945
01:03:36,230 --> 01:03:37,565
What happened to you?

946
01:03:37,648 --> 01:03:39,734
Charbroiled by Death, apparently.

947
01:03:39,817 --> 01:03:41,777
- Kiki, that looks really bad.
- Yeah, it's fine.

948
01:03:41,861 --> 01:03:43,613
No, wait. Let me see that.

949
01:03:43,696 --> 01:03:45,948
- Erik, just stay away from the truck.
- Stop.

950
01:03:46,991 --> 01:03:48,201
- Oh, what, this truck?
- Stop!

951
01:03:48,284 --> 01:03:49,577
- Oh my God.
- Please.

952
01:03:49,660 --> 01:03:50,578
This truck right here?

953
01:03:50,661 --> 01:03:52,038
Please just
listen to me for one...

954
01:03:52,121 --> 01:03:53,206
But it's such a beautiful truck.

955
01:03:53,289 --> 01:03:54,624
Please. Stop, stop.
Don't touch...

956
01:03:54,707 --> 01:03:56,209
- Mwah!
- Erik, get away!

957
01:03:56,292 --> 01:03:57,376
Stop!

958
01:03:58,252 --> 01:03:59,587
- You like that?
- Can you just...

959
01:04:00,254 --> 01:04:01,631
Oh my God.

960
01:04:02,423 --> 01:04:04,383
Oh! Uh-oh.

961
01:04:04,467 --> 01:04:06,511
Oh, Erik's tempting Death again.

962
01:04:06,594 --> 01:04:08,012
What's going to happen?

963
01:04:08,095 --> 01:04:11,724
- Stop doing that!
- What is going to happen?

964
01:04:12,725 --> 01:04:14,477
- Nothing at all.
- Please, just...

965
01:04:14,560 --> 01:04:15,561
How about that?

966
01:04:15,645 --> 01:04:16,979
Look,
I'm just trying to help you.

967
01:04:17,063 --> 01:04:18,856
- Okay.
- Try less.

968
01:04:18,940 --> 01:04:21,567
Yeah. Honestly, we're so done
with your garbage.

969
01:04:22,443 --> 01:04:24,946
- Can you please...
- Okay, for the 1,500th time,

970
01:04:25,029 --> 01:04:27,448
no one gives a shit about
your stupid little Death curse, okay?

971
01:04:27,532 --> 01:04:29,492
So take a hint and leave us alone

972
01:04:29,575 --> 01:04:31,494
because Death's
not coming for our family!

973
01:04:36,832 --> 01:04:37,875
Julia!

974
01:04:37,959 --> 01:04:39,043
Shit.

975
01:04:42,171 --> 01:04:43,923
- Julia!
- Julia!

976
01:04:44,006 --> 01:04:45,341
- Julia!
- Julia!

977
01:04:45,424 --> 01:04:48,636
Stop the truck! Stop the truck!

978
01:05:00,273 --> 01:05:02,275
- Stop the truck!
- Hey! Hey!

979
01:05:02,358 --> 01:05:03,442
Stop the fucking truck!

980
01:05:03,526 --> 01:05:04,986
My sister's in the garbage!

981
01:05:06,320 --> 01:05:07,697
<i>♪ What doesn't kill you
Makes you stronger ♪</i>

982
01:05:07,780 --> 01:05:09,865
<i>♪ Stand a little taller ♪</i>

983
01:05:09,949 --> 01:05:11,993
<i>♪ Doesn't mean I'm lonely
When I'm alone ♪</i>

984
01:05:13,661 --> 01:05:16,163
<i>♪ What doesn't kill you
Makes a fighter ♪</i>

985
01:05:16,247 --> 01:05:17,748
<i>♪ Footsteps even lighter... ♪</i>

986
01:05:24,755 --> 01:05:26,549
- Help!

987
01:05:26,632 --> 01:05:27,800
- Julia?
- Stef!

988
01:05:27,883 --> 01:05:29,427
Give me your hand!

989
01:05:29,510 --> 01:05:30,720
I got you!

990
01:05:30,803 --> 01:05:32,305
Don't worry, you're not next!

991
01:05:32,388 --> 01:05:33,681
Whoa! Whoa!

992
01:05:33,764 --> 01:05:36,309
- Help!
- Hey, stop! Stop!

993
01:05:37,101 --> 01:05:38,352
- Stop!
- Stop!

994
01:05:38,436 --> 01:05:40,271
- Stop! Stop!
- Stop!

995
01:05:41,731 --> 01:05:43,357
- My sister's in the back!
- Stef!

996
01:06:00,916 --> 01:06:03,252
- I'm so sorry, sweetie.
- Dad.

997
01:06:12,595 --> 01:06:14,055
We should've believed you, Stef.

998
01:06:17,141 --> 01:06:18,351
No, I...

999
01:06:20,770 --> 01:06:24,106
I screwed up the order
and now Julia's dead and it's my fault.

1000
01:06:25,024 --> 01:06:30,029
Guys, look. What happened
was traumatic and awful.

1001
01:06:30,112 --> 01:06:31,781
- It's not anybody's fault.
- Marty, please don't.

1002
01:06:34,533 --> 01:06:35,534
It's my fault.

1003
01:06:36,661 --> 01:06:37,912
Mom, it's not your fault.

1004
01:06:37,995 --> 01:06:39,372
It is my fault.

1005
01:06:41,707 --> 01:06:43,876
Stefani, you were only wrong
about the order

1006
01:06:43,959 --> 01:06:45,753
because there is something
you didn't know.

1007
01:06:50,549 --> 01:06:53,803
Erik isn't Howard's biological son.

1008
01:06:56,889 --> 01:06:58,974
I'm sorry. What are you talking about?

1009
01:06:59,058 --> 01:07:00,893
And Stefani, I didn't believe you,

1010
01:07:00,976 --> 01:07:04,355
so I didn't say anything to you,
and now my little girl is dead.

1011
01:07:04,438 --> 01:07:06,232
I don't understand.
What, you had an affair?

1012
01:07:06,816 --> 01:07:09,527
Your father and I were
having such a hard time...

1013
01:07:10,403 --> 01:07:12,988
but it was good because I got you.
I got you out of it.

1014
01:07:13,072 --> 01:07:14,407
Who's my real dad then?
Who's my real dad?

1015
01:07:14,490 --> 01:07:17,118
It doesn't matter
because Howard loved you so, so much.

1016
01:07:17,201 --> 01:07:18,202
Who is it?

1017
01:07:20,413 --> 01:07:21,455
Who's my real dad?

1018
01:07:24,917 --> 01:07:25,918
Jerry Fenbury.

1019
01:07:28,546 --> 01:07:29,964
Jerry Fenbury?

1020
01:07:30,047 --> 01:07:31,340
Yes.

1021
01:07:31,424 --> 01:07:32,842
Oh, shit.

1022
01:07:32,925 --> 01:07:34,009
- No, no, no!
- Erik.

1023
01:07:34,093 --> 01:07:35,594
Jerry fucking Fenbury?

1024
01:07:35,678 --> 01:07:37,763
You don't know
what we were going through.

1025
01:07:37,847 --> 01:07:40,433
Oh, God! What, is this why
he always wanted to play catch?

1026
01:07:40,516 --> 01:07:42,017
Oh my God.

1027
01:07:47,481 --> 01:07:48,607
Okay.

1028
01:07:49,483 --> 01:07:53,779
All right, so, that means that
if it's going in the right order that...

1029
01:07:55,156 --> 01:07:56,157
I'm next, right?

1030
01:08:02,955 --> 01:08:04,623
You got to help me, Stef.

1031
01:08:05,708 --> 01:08:08,085
Bobby, I don't...
I don't think that I can.

1032
01:08:08,169 --> 01:08:10,296
I mean, I thought I did,
but I don't know...

1033
01:08:10,379 --> 01:08:12,840
No. But you can.

1034
01:08:14,216 --> 01:08:16,802
I mean, you predicted
exactly what was going to happen.

1035
01:08:18,304 --> 01:08:19,388
You just got the order wrong

1036
01:08:19,472 --> 01:08:20,806
because you didn't
have all the information.

1037
01:08:20,890 --> 01:08:22,850
- Charlie.
- What do you mean "predicted"?

1038
01:08:23,601 --> 01:08:25,519
She saw everything.

1039
01:08:25,603 --> 01:08:28,689
The trimmer, the blower,
the soccer ball.

1040
01:08:28,773 --> 01:08:32,318
It was like they were pieces to a puzzle
and she just had to put them together.

1041
01:08:32,401 --> 01:08:33,903
- You know what I mean?
- Is that true?

1042
01:08:33,986 --> 01:08:35,196
Darlene, please.

1043
01:08:35,279 --> 01:08:37,782
- Do not encourage this.
- Marty.

1044
01:08:37,865 --> 01:08:39,283
I mean...

1045
01:08:40,159 --> 01:08:42,828
I mean,
it's everything in Iris's book. It's...

1046
01:08:42,912 --> 01:08:45,831
It's like an equation. It's math.

1047
01:08:45,915 --> 01:08:48,876
Stefani, if you can see
how all of this fits together,

1048
01:08:48,959 --> 01:08:50,211
we might have a chance.

1049
01:08:50,294 --> 01:08:51,796
Stop. Just stop.

1050
01:08:52,922 --> 01:08:55,549
You devastated this family
when you walked out.

1051
01:08:55,633 --> 01:08:57,802
But we've been okay without you.

1052
01:08:57,885 --> 01:09:01,138
I'm begging you
not to traumatize our kids anymore.

1053
01:09:01,931 --> 01:09:03,182
It's real this time.

1054
01:09:07,770 --> 01:09:09,688
I'm going for a walk.

1055
01:09:10,272 --> 01:09:11,315
I need some air.

1056
01:09:16,612 --> 01:09:18,948
I can appreciate that

1057
01:09:19,031 --> 01:09:22,034
our family is clearly going to need
some counseling in the future,

1058
01:09:22,117 --> 01:09:26,372
but can we focus on the fact
that we're all about to die, right?

1059
01:09:26,455 --> 01:09:29,083
I mean... I mean, Stef,

1060
01:09:29,166 --> 01:09:32,169
didn't you say that... that Iris...

1061
01:09:32,253 --> 01:09:34,505
knew someone
that cheated death or something?

1062
01:09:34,588 --> 01:09:35,714
Yeah, um...

1063
01:09:37,049 --> 01:09:40,135
In here, somewhere, it says...

1064
01:09:41,887 --> 01:09:43,889
that, uh... Right here.

1065
01:09:43,973 --> 01:09:45,724
"JB found someone who survived."

1066
01:09:45,808 --> 01:09:49,103
But it doesn't say anything
about who this JB was or...

1067
01:09:49,186 --> 01:09:51,105
Wait a minute. I know that name.

1068
01:09:51,188 --> 01:09:52,731
My mom used to write me letters,

1069
01:09:52,815 --> 01:09:56,068
and she sometimes would talk
about a friend of hers named JB

1070
01:09:56,151 --> 01:09:58,237
who worked at a hospital.

1071
01:09:58,320 --> 01:09:59,405
Hospital.

1072
01:09:59,488 --> 01:10:00,990
Um... um...

1073
01:10:01,073 --> 01:10:04,243
Something, uh...
Something River Hospital.

1074
01:10:04,326 --> 01:10:05,828
Uh, Deep River.

1075
01:10:05,911 --> 01:10:08,622
Uh, Peace River Hospital. Clear River...

1076
01:10:08,706 --> 01:10:10,666
- Hope River?
- That's it!

1077
01:10:11,375 --> 01:10:12,877
Shit, it's like an hour away.

1078
01:10:12,960 --> 01:10:15,421
I'm going. I'm going to go find him
and talk to him myself.

1079
01:10:15,504 --> 01:10:16,839
Well, I'm coming with you.

1080
01:10:16,922 --> 01:10:19,383
- Me too.
- Okay. Yeah, yeah, let's go.

1081
01:10:21,343 --> 01:10:22,428
Bobby, uh...

1082
01:10:22,511 --> 01:10:24,096
What?

1083
01:10:24,179 --> 01:10:26,515
You need to stay here with your mom.
It's safer.

1084
01:10:26,599 --> 01:10:28,392
Yeah, fuck that.

1085
01:10:28,475 --> 01:10:30,477
Are you kidding me?
I'm not staying here by myself.

1086
01:10:30,561 --> 01:10:32,688
Well, it's too dangerous
on the road for you. You can't.

1087
01:10:32,771 --> 01:10:36,150
No, I read Gammy's Death Book, okay?
All right?

1088
01:10:36,233 --> 01:10:40,154
I mean, there's like a thousand
house-related deaths in that thing, man.

1089
01:10:40,237 --> 01:10:42,031
You can trip down the stairs,

1090
01:10:42,114 --> 01:10:45,075
fall down a toilet or something.

1091
01:10:45,159 --> 01:10:47,870
I don't know, but I'm not...
No way. I'm not staying here.

1092
01:10:49,705 --> 01:10:51,498
- Hang on, hang on.
- Hey, okay.

1093
01:10:51,582 --> 01:10:52,583
- Okay.
- Too fast.

1094
01:10:52,666 --> 01:10:53,959
Okay, okay.
We'll go slow. We'll go slow.

1095
01:10:54,043 --> 01:10:55,127
I'm going to go open up the truck.

1096
01:10:55,210 --> 01:10:56,587
- Charlie, check the back.
- Got it.

1097
01:10:56,670 --> 01:10:57,546
Okay.

1098
01:11:02,051 --> 01:11:03,844
Be careful.
The step's slippery sometimes.

1099
01:11:03,928 --> 01:11:05,137
- Oi!

1100
01:11:07,139 --> 01:11:09,058
Any of you fuckers do a nut check?

1101
01:11:10,017 --> 01:11:10,976
Excuse me?

1102
01:11:11,060 --> 01:11:12,519
You made cookies in that thing

1103
01:11:12,603 --> 01:11:14,188
with peanut butter in them
just a few days ago.

1104
01:11:15,439 --> 01:11:17,983
This poor bastard
so much as even touches a nut,

1105
01:11:18,067 --> 01:11:19,777
his throat is going to close up
tighter than...

1106
01:11:20,694 --> 01:11:22,488
You understand.
Where's the peanut butter?

1107
01:11:22,571 --> 01:11:24,865
- Cabinet above the sink.
- Thank you.

1108
01:11:26,200 --> 01:11:28,160
I'm so sorry, Bobby. I just...

1109
01:11:29,119 --> 01:11:30,120
Yeah.

1110
01:11:30,955 --> 01:11:32,081
Hey. Okay.

1111
01:11:35,000 --> 01:11:36,251
All clear.

1112
01:11:36,335 --> 01:11:39,004
Thank you. You're a good brother, Erik.

1113
01:11:39,630 --> 01:11:40,631
- Nut check.
- What?

1114
01:11:40,714 --> 01:11:43,092
- God!
- Stupid.

1115
01:11:45,803 --> 01:11:47,471
It was good. I get it.

1116
01:11:47,554 --> 01:11:48,847
Let's go. Come on.

1117
01:11:48,931 --> 01:11:50,975
It's only going to get worse.

1118
01:11:51,058 --> 01:11:52,059
Goddamn it.

1119
01:11:52,142 --> 01:11:55,270
Wait! I'm coming with you, bro.

1120
01:11:55,354 --> 01:11:57,064
Someone's got to protect you.

1121
01:12:04,738 --> 01:12:07,116
Dad's calling. Again.

1122
01:12:07,199 --> 01:12:08,784
Tell him we just
went for a ride with Mom.

1123
01:12:08,867 --> 01:12:10,160
He's not going to believe that.

1124
01:12:10,244 --> 01:12:12,204
At least it'll buy us some time.

1125
01:12:12,287 --> 01:12:13,288
All right.

1126
01:12:15,708 --> 01:12:17,543
If Death doesn't get us, your dad will.

1127
01:12:30,264 --> 01:12:31,974
I always keep them where I can see them.

1128
01:12:34,893 --> 01:12:36,854
I mean, you could've just
had the real thing,

1129
01:12:36,937 --> 01:12:38,689
but it's okay,
not everyone wants to be a mom.

1130
01:12:41,775 --> 01:12:43,318
Is that what you think?

1131
01:12:43,402 --> 01:12:45,362
That I didn't want to be your mom?

1132
01:12:47,906 --> 01:12:53,328
Look, I was raised by a woman
who taught me to see Death everywhere.

1133
01:12:54,288 --> 01:12:55,789
I thought I could put it behind me,

1134
01:12:55,873 --> 01:12:58,167
but then when I had you
and your brother,

1135
01:12:58,250 --> 01:13:00,669
all I could see were
a hundred different ways

1136
01:13:00,753 --> 01:13:02,713
that you and Charlie could die.

1137
01:13:03,464 --> 01:13:05,549
I didn't want you to leave the house.

1138
01:13:05,632 --> 01:13:08,927
I would freak out on you guys
over nothing.

1139
01:13:10,429 --> 01:13:11,722
One day I looked at your face

1140
01:13:11,805 --> 01:13:15,601
and I saw the same scared little girl
that I was growing up,

1141
01:13:15,684 --> 01:13:18,437
and I knew that if I stayed,
I was going to ruin your life.

1142
01:13:21,106 --> 01:13:23,192
I have no idea if I did the right thing.

1143
01:13:24,651 --> 01:13:25,903
But I'm here for you now.

1144
01:13:50,594 --> 01:13:51,553
It's okay.

1145
01:13:52,387 --> 01:13:53,472
I'm right behind you.

1146
01:14:05,275 --> 01:14:07,569
Hey. Now you see, buddy. We got you.

1147
01:14:07,653 --> 01:14:09,238
The front desk is this way.

1148
01:14:14,743 --> 01:14:19,915
Oh. Hi. We're looking for JB.

1149
01:14:20,749 --> 01:14:21,959
And who are you?

1150
01:14:22,709 --> 01:14:25,420
The front desk told us we could
find him down here. Is that you?

1151
01:14:25,504 --> 01:14:27,840
That would be me.

1152
01:14:37,516 --> 01:14:41,979
William John Bludworth.
But my friends call me JB.

1153
01:14:42,062 --> 01:14:45,566
I've been waiting for you, Stefani.

1154
01:14:45,649 --> 01:14:47,818
Charlie. Darlene.

1155
01:14:47,901 --> 01:14:50,445
But no Howard. No Julia.

1156
01:14:51,572 --> 01:14:54,575
So, which one of you is next?

1157
01:14:58,579 --> 01:14:59,580
Hi.

1158
01:14:59,663 --> 01:15:02,499
I was sorry to hear about Iris.

1159
01:15:02,583 --> 01:15:04,710
She was a special woman.

1160
01:15:05,502 --> 01:15:06,587
How did you know her?

1161
01:15:07,379 --> 01:15:09,089
She saved my life.

1162
01:15:09,965 --> 01:15:10,966
When?

1163
01:15:13,177 --> 01:15:14,761
At the Sky View.

1164
01:15:19,766 --> 01:15:22,311
<i>My mother brought me
with her to work that night.</i>

1165
01:15:22,394 --> 01:15:23,979
JB, honey, I told you,

1166
01:15:24,062 --> 01:15:26,315
you got to stay back there
while I'm on stage.

1167
01:15:26,398 --> 01:15:28,066
<i>I wasn't
supposed to be there,</i>

1168
01:15:28,150 --> 01:15:30,611
<i>except, of course, to die.</i>

1169
01:15:30,694 --> 01:15:32,613
<i>- ♪ You know you make me wanna ♪
- ♪ Shout ♪</i>

1170
01:15:32,696 --> 01:15:34,323
<i>- ♪ Kick my heels up and ♪
- ♪ Shout ♪</i>

1171
01:15:34,406 --> 01:15:37,159
<i>- ♪ Throw my hands up and ♪</i>
- Stop playing! Stop playing!

1172
01:15:37,242 --> 01:15:39,494
<i>Everyone needs to get off
the dance floor!</i>

1173
01:15:39,578 --> 01:15:41,914
<i>The glass is about to break.
Everyone needs to get off now!</i>

1174
01:15:41,997 --> 01:15:43,332
Wait! No!

1175
01:15:43,415 --> 01:15:44,791
Iris!

1176
01:15:55,052 --> 01:15:56,970
You were the last to die.
You were the little boy.

1177
01:15:58,972 --> 01:16:00,098
Correct.

1178
01:16:00,182 --> 01:16:01,475
So, all that time,

1179
01:16:01,558 --> 01:16:04,478
she wasn't just protecting our family,

1180
01:16:04,561 --> 01:16:06,021
she was protecting you too.

1181
01:16:07,105 --> 01:16:09,733
Years later, she tracked me down.

1182
01:16:09,816 --> 01:16:12,110
Helped me see the truth.

1183
01:16:12,194 --> 01:16:14,112
We traded ideas.

1184
01:16:14,196 --> 01:16:16,698
I helped her fortify her cabin.

1185
01:16:16,782 --> 01:16:18,325
We became friends.

1186
01:16:18,909 --> 01:16:22,663
I even helped her
get the best medical care I could,

1187
01:16:22,746 --> 01:16:24,373
considering her condition.

1188
01:16:24,456 --> 01:16:28,126
Iris said that you found somebody
who stopped Death and survived.

1189
01:16:28,210 --> 01:16:29,628
Yes.

1190
01:16:29,711 --> 01:16:32,214
Uh, and how do we do that?

1191
01:16:32,297 --> 01:16:34,216
There are only two ways.

1192
01:16:34,299 --> 01:16:37,511
By killing or by dying.

1193
01:16:37,594 --> 01:16:41,890
If you take a life,
you get the time that person had left.

1194
01:16:41,974 --> 01:16:44,559
What? No!
I... I'm not going to kill someone.

1195
01:16:44,643 --> 01:16:46,270
Maybe we should let the guy finish.

1196
01:16:46,353 --> 01:16:50,107
And to truly break the cycle,
you have to die.

1197
01:16:50,190 --> 01:16:52,484
What... What does that mean?

1198
01:16:53,485 --> 01:16:57,739
A long time ago,
a young woman named Kimberly Corman

1199
01:16:57,823 --> 01:16:59,908
found herself on Death's list.

1200
01:16:59,992 --> 01:17:01,952
Just like you.

1201
01:17:02,035 --> 01:17:05,747
And when her turn finally came,
she died.

1202
01:17:05,831 --> 01:17:06,957
Flatlined.

1203
01:17:07,040 --> 01:17:09,501
But her doctor managed
to bring her back,

1204
01:17:09,584 --> 01:17:12,296
and that broke the chain.

1205
01:17:12,379 --> 01:17:14,881
- All right, then. We'll do that.
- What are you talking about?

1206
01:17:16,717 --> 01:17:18,677
Why didn't Iris try that?

1207
01:17:18,760 --> 01:17:19,928
It's risky.

1208
01:17:20,012 --> 01:17:23,348
And if you fuck with Death and lose,

1209
01:17:23,432 --> 01:17:26,727
things can get very messy.

1210
01:17:29,354 --> 01:17:32,899
Wait. Hang on, hang on. Okay, wait. No.

1211
01:17:32,983 --> 01:17:35,485
There has to be another way.
Please, you have to help us.

1212
01:17:36,236 --> 01:17:39,531
For years, people have been
coming to me for advice.

1213
01:17:40,490 --> 01:17:43,994
Well, I'm tired. I'm done with all that.

1214
01:17:44,077 --> 01:17:46,246
And now, I'm sick just like Iris.

1215
01:17:46,330 --> 01:17:48,874
There's no running this time.

1216
01:17:48,957 --> 01:17:52,711
Fact is, you're all going to die.

1217
01:17:52,794 --> 01:17:55,630
And after that, I will too.

1218
01:17:59,384 --> 01:18:02,262
Now that my old friend is gone,
I'm retiring.

1219
01:18:02,346 --> 01:18:04,056
So, what,
you're just gonna leave us here?

1220
01:18:04,139 --> 01:18:05,891
- Wait, wait, wait!
- Dude, we need your help.

1221
01:18:05,974 --> 01:18:07,059
Where are you going?

1222
01:18:07,142 --> 01:18:10,812
I intend to enjoy the time I have left.

1223
01:18:11,396 --> 01:18:14,900
And I suggest that you do the same.

1224
01:18:14,983 --> 01:18:16,568
Life is precious.

1225
01:18:18,403 --> 01:18:20,655
Enjoy every single second.

1226
01:18:21,740 --> 01:18:23,200
You never know when.

1227
01:18:29,039 --> 01:18:30,123
Good luck.

1228
01:18:36,004 --> 01:18:37,422
Well, that's fantastic.

1229
01:18:38,423 --> 01:18:40,384
- No. No.
- Bobby.

1230
01:18:40,467 --> 01:18:44,096
No, that... that can't be it.
No. No, there...

1231
01:18:44,179 --> 01:18:47,265
There has to be something here.
There has to be another answer.

1232
01:18:47,349 --> 01:18:51,770
Stef. Stef. Stef, he gave us an answer.

1233
01:18:51,853 --> 01:18:53,480
Bobby's got to die.

1234
01:18:53,563 --> 01:18:54,523
Erik!

1235
01:18:54,606 --> 01:18:57,150
Are you fucking insane?
We're not killing Bobby!

1236
01:18:57,234 --> 01:18:59,861
Whoa, whoa, am I the only guy
that just listened to that dude?

1237
01:18:59,945 --> 01:19:00,862
There's only one way.

1238
01:19:00,946 --> 01:19:02,864
We kill Bobby, we resuscitate him,

1239
01:19:02,948 --> 01:19:04,908
and then boom,
you're all off Death's list.

1240
01:19:04,991 --> 01:19:05,909
Congratulations.

1241
01:19:05,992 --> 01:19:07,494
There has to be something else, right?

1242
01:19:07,577 --> 01:19:09,871
I mean, there has to be
another solution, right, Stef?

1243
01:19:11,081 --> 01:19:12,082
No.

1244
01:19:12,958 --> 01:19:15,252
No, there's...
there's nothing else we can do, okay?

1245
01:19:15,335 --> 01:19:16,336
It's over.

1246
01:19:17,671 --> 01:19:18,922
Hey.

1247
01:19:19,005 --> 01:19:20,340
Stefani, listen to me.

1248
01:19:20,424 --> 01:19:21,967
You got to trust me on this one, okay?

1249
01:19:22,050 --> 01:19:24,261
She's giving up on you,
I'm not going to.

1250
01:19:24,344 --> 01:19:27,973
Look, Iris found a way
to hold Death off for decades.

1251
01:19:30,600 --> 01:19:32,269
- So will we.
- I trust that guy.

1252
01:19:32,352 --> 01:19:33,562
You trust that guy?

1253
01:19:33,645 --> 01:19:34,980
- He was...
- This one that...

1254
01:19:35,063 --> 01:19:38,608
He was awfully charismatic,
and you know that as well as I do...

1255
01:19:50,203 --> 01:19:51,329
Uh...

1256
01:19:52,164 --> 01:19:53,874
Erik and Bobby are gone.

1257
01:19:54,791 --> 01:19:56,626
Shit. Shit!

1258
01:19:58,295 --> 01:19:59,296
I don't think I like this.

1259
01:19:59,379 --> 01:20:01,256
Hey, dude,
we're in a hospital, remember?

1260
01:20:01,339 --> 01:20:02,466
There's doctors everywhere.

1261
01:20:02,549 --> 01:20:04,593
We kill you, they bring you back,

1262
01:20:04,676 --> 01:20:07,095
everybody's safe, we're heroes.

1263
01:20:07,179 --> 01:20:09,473
Dude, that is literally
the opposite of keeping me safe.

1264
01:20:09,556 --> 01:20:10,765
What's the alternative, huh?

1265
